.claude

# Evidence bundle output — covers the README's example path
# (`--out-dir ./evidence`). `--out-dir` is user-chosen, so this rule
# only helps repos that follow that convention. The authoritative
# guidance is still: point `--out-dir` outside the tracked tree
# (`/tmp/evidence`, `$RUNNER_TEMP/evidence` in CI, …). See README
# "Choosing --out-dir" for why.
/evidence/

# Nix build output symlinks produced by `nix build`. Safe to ignore —
# they are GC roots into /nix/store, not artifacts worth tracking.
/result
/result-*